applyAllowlistedTargetsUpdates.t.sol
├─ when the caller does not have the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE
│  └─ it should revert
└─ when the caller has the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE
   ├─ when the workflow ID is not allowlisted
   │  └─ it should revert
   └─ when the workflow ID is allowlisted
      ├─ when both removes and adds are empty
      │  └─ it should revert
      └─ when either removes or adds are not empty
         ├─ when a removed target is not allowlisted for the workflow ID
         │  └─ it should revert
         ├─ when an added target is address zero
         │  └─ it should revert
         ├─ when only removing targets
         │  ├─ it should remove the targets from the allowlist
         │  ├─ it should clean up all selectors for the removed targets
         │  └─ it should emit the correct events
         ├─ when only adding targets
         │  ├─ it should allowlist the targets and selectors
         │  └─ it should emit the correct events
         └─ when adding and removing targets in the same call
            ├─ it should process removes before adds
            └─ it should emit the correct events
